CONTEXT EnforceAssignment IN ENGLISH
-- Negative test: a real `ENFORCE r := expr` statement. The compiler lowers it to
-- an insert rule (`expr |- r`) and a delete rule (`r |- expr`) maintained by the
-- ExecEngine — a non-monotone cycle on `r`. But it computes `r := expr` for an
-- `expr` the cycle never rewrites, so it converges. This MUST stay silent, which
-- also checks that the certificate fires for the ENFORCE syntax itself, not only
-- for the hand-written Determine/Remove idiom.

RELATION worksFor[Person*Company] [UNI]
RELATION locatedIn[Company*City] [UNI]
RELATION basedIn[Person*City] [UNI]

ENFORCE basedIn := worksFor;locatedIn

ENDCONTEXT
